    <question>
        <prompt>How did the "Poll Tax" affect voting rights?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Prevented poor citizens from voting through fees</option>
            <option letter="b">Increased voter participation</option>
            <option letter="c">Protected voting rights</option>
            <option letter="d">Improved election security</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Poll Tax effectively prevented many poor citizens, especially African Americans, from voting by requiring payment of a fee to vote.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
        <prompt>What was the significance of the "Force Bill" of 1871?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Gave presidents power to combat Klan violence</option>
            <option letter="b">Restricted federal authority</option>
            <option letter="c">Protected Confederate rights</option>
            <option letter="d">Regulated commerce</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Force Bill gave presidents the authority to use military force to combat Ku Klux Klan violence and protect civil rights.</explanation>
    </question>
